INSERT INTO `nc_posts` VALUES (1,1,'2012-10-08 03:12:51','2012-10-08 03:12:51','Welcome to WordPress. This is your first post. Edit or delete it, then start blogging!','Hello world!','','trash','open','open','','hello-world','','','2012-10-11 00:37:31','2012-10-10 15:37:31','',0,'http://aus-newcastle/?p=1',0,'post','',1),(15,1,'2012-10-09 05:39:15','2012-10-09 05:39:15','As the largest city in Hunter Region and the second oldest city in New South Wales, Newcastle is rich in history with heritage buildings. This city rests on a peninsula bordered by the splendid working harbour. You can expect to see remarkable surfing and beaches. What’s more, the city of Newcastle offers Visitor Information Centres just for you.\r\nExplore the suburbs of Newcastle and see a great deal of diversity among them – from the heritage buildings and streets in Newcastle East, nightlife spot in City Centre, and impressive exhibitions at Theatres and Galleries in the Civic Cultural Precinct.\r\n\r\nThere are so many things to see and do in the great city of Newcastle. With our useful guide below, planning for a holiday in this lovely city is made simpler for you.\r\n<h3><strong>Local Visitor Information Centre</strong></h3>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>Free Call 1800 654 558</strong>\r\nWebsite: <a href=\"http://tourism@ncc.nsw.gov.au\" target=\"_blank\">tourism@ncc.nsw.gov.au</a></p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>Maritime Centre</strong>\r\n3 Honeysuckle Drive\r\nNewcastle, NSW 2300\r\nOpen 9.30am – 4.30pm Tuesday – Sunday</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\"><strong>Hunter Wetlands Centre</strong>\r\n412 Sandgate Road\r\nShortland, NSW 2307\r\nOpen 9.00am – 4.00pm Weekdays\r\nOpen 9.00am – 5.00pm Weekends</p>\r\n<p style=\"padding-left: 30px;\">Both centres are closed on Christmas Day and Good Friday.\r\nCall the freecall number for other public holidays.</p>','Tourist Information','','publish','open','open','','tourist-information','','','2012-10-12 16:32:5