lt=\"\" width=\"433\" height=\"219\" /></a>From the mainland, a very narrow finger of land extends out to the hill called the Nobbys Head. Nobbys Head, a headland, is a famous landmark located on the south side of the entrance to Newcastle Harbour. It is currently standing at 28m above sea level, and it is now an attractive long spit. Nobbys Head was an island before it joined the mainland in 1846. It was originally called Coal Island in 1801.</p>\r\nAlthough Newcastle East is the home of Nobbys beach, the Nobbys Head is technically not in the suburb. A lighthouse sits on the Nobbys Head which was established in 1854. It is the third lighthouse built in New South Wales. For 150 years, it has stood guard over the Newcastle harbor entrance.\r\n<h2 style=\"text-align: right;\">Aerial Shot</h2>\r\n<a href=\"http://aus-newcastle.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/web-nobbys-headland.jpg\"><img class=\"wp-image-131 alignright\" title=\"web-nobbys-headland\" src=\"http://aus-newcastle.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/web-nobbys-headland.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"198\" height=\"132\" /></a>\r\n\r\nThe grounds are available for free public access between 10am and 4pm during the first and third Sunday of every month. The Nobbys Head is available for private hire for small weddings, wedding photographs, special occasions, and corporate functions.\r\n\r\nNobbys head is a great place to have fun. You can enjoy swimming in the beach, and fishing, kite surfing. Furthermore, you can also take pleasure in the magnificent views of the city and Pacific Ocean.\r\n\r\n<strong>Contact for Booking Information:</strong>\r\n<strong>Phone:</strong> 0249 253 969\r\n<strong>Email:</strong> livesites@ncc.nsw.gov.au','Nobbys Headland','','publish','open','open','','nobbys-headland','','','2012-10-10 23:44:01','2012-10-10 14:44:01','',102,'http://aus-newcastle.com/?page_id=119',0,'page','',0),(120,1,'2012-10-10 23:03:49','2012-10-10 14:03:49','','NOBBYS HEADLAND','','inherit','open','open','','119-revisio