10 14:42:20','',119,'http://aus-newcastle.com/archives/142',0,'revision','',0),(143,1,'2012-10-10 23:45:21','2012-10-10 14:45:21','One of the advantages of being a port city is the easy access of beaches. Newcastle has both an amazing city and best beaches. What’s more, with a unique history, there are many heritage buildings and icons that you could visit in the centre.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_151\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"362\"]<a href=\"http://aus-newcastle.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/800px-VictoriaTheatre2007.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-151 \" title=\"VictoriaTheatre\" src=\"http://aus-newcastle.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/800px-VictoriaTheatre2007-750x380.jpg\" alt=\"VictoriaTheatre\" width=\"362\" height=\"190\" /></a> VictoriaTheatre[/caption]\r\n\r\nNewcastle City Centre is a combination of three suburbs known as Newcastle, Newcastle East, and Newcastle West. The city centre is the home of popular precincts such as the Civic Cultural Precinct and the Honeysuckle precinct. The city centre is the main nightlife spot. You can go shopping in the Hunter Street Mall which has many shopping outlets. You can easily walk around the CBD since it is walk-able in size.\r\n\r\nVisit the large collection of restaurants, bars, and other sorts of entertainment in Queens Wharf. Take a peek in the galleries, enjoy picnics and BBQs in one of the parks, or take a show at the theatres. Experience the Famous Tram, bus tours, or simply walking for sightseeing around the city centre.\r\n\r\nThe city centre boasts of 1400 shops and businesses. There are many different districts where you can find amazing fashion boutiques, surf shops, ski and snowboard outlets, fine food halls, and wonderful markets.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://aus-newcastle.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/010.jpg\"><img class=\"alignright size-medium wp-image-155\" title=\" Shepherds Hill\" src=\"http://aus-newcastle.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/010-300x199.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" /></a>There are many places you could visit in the city centre. You can relax and look around at the Shepherds Hill Cottage Reserve, located at the Terrace, is attached to King Edward Park. There are toilet amenities and the reserve is connected to several walkways. Visit the Victoria theatre which is the oldest facility, over 100 years old, of the kind in Newcastle, the oldest surviving theatre building in NSW and is currently unoccupied. Or you could dine out at notable restaurants and bars such as The Brewery, Customs House Bar and Restaurant, Bacchus Restaurant, and Sprocket Roasters.\r\n\r\n[caption id=\"attachment_161\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"470\"]<a href=\"http://aus-newcastle.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/sheperds-hill.jpg\"><img class=\" wp-image-161 \" title=\"sheperds-hill\" src=\"http://aus-newcastle.com/wp-content/uploads/2012/10/sheperds-hill-470x260.jpg\" alt=\"\" width=\"470\" height=\"260\" /></a> Shepherds Hill[/caption]\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Newcastle City Centre','','publish','open','open','','newcastle-city-centre','','','2012-10-11 00:10:49','2012-10-10 15:10:49','',102,'http://aus-newcastle.com/?page_id=143',1,'page','',0),(144,1,'2012-10-10 23:45:12','2012-10-10 14:45:12','One of the advantages of being a port city is the easy access of beaches. Newcastle has both an amazing city and best beaches. What’s more, with a unique history, there are many heritage buildings and icons that you could visit in the centre.\nNewcastle City Centre is a combination of three suburbs known as Newcastle, Newcastle East, and Newcastle West. The city centre is the home of popular precincts such as the Civic Cultural Precinct and the Honeysuckle precinct. The city centre is the main nightlife spot. You can go shopping in the Hunter Street Mall which has many shopping outlets. You can easily walk around the CBD since it is walk-able in size.\nVisit the large collection of restaurants, bars, and other sorts of entertainment in Queens Wharf. Take a peek in the ga