est ocean bath in NSW, and it has been enlarged since the 1820s. The Bogey Hole was hewn out of a rock face at 1819 to 1884 by convicts. Originally as “Commandant’s Bath”, the Bogey Hole is a purpose build ocean swimming pool for the personal use of a notable military figure, Major James Morisset.\r\n\r\nThe Bogey Hole is a famous swimming spot, an icon of the city. It can be located just beneath the headland in King Edward Park. The place provides an amazing view of the Newcastle coastline. You can get to enjoy seeing the waves crashing into the pool. Indeed, the Bogey Hole is a favorite not only for the visitors but also for the locals. It is a popular site for photographers and other artists. Enjoy the view of the Bogey Hole from dawn till dusk every day.','Bogey Hole - Newcastle','','inherit','open','open','','221-revision-3','','','2012-10-12 13:19:17','2012-10-12 04:19:17','',221,'http://localhost/aus-newcastle/archives/263',0,'revision','',0),(264,1,'2012-10-12 13:21:16','2012-10-12 04:21:16','<strong>The Bogey is located at Shortland Esplande of Newcastle</strong>. It is the oldest ocean bath in NSW, and it has been enlarged since the 1820s. The Bogey Hole was hewn out of a rock face at 1819 to 1884 by convicts. Originally as “Commandant’s Bath”, the Bogey Hole is a purpose build ocean swimming pool for the personal use of a notable military figure, Major James Morisset.\r\n\r\nThe Bogey Hole is a famous swimming spot, an icon of the city. It can be located just beneath the headland in King Edward Park. The place provides an amazing view of the Newcastle coastline. You can get to enjoy seeing the waves crashing into the pool. Indeed, the Bogey Hole is a favorite not only for the visitors but also for the locals. It is a popular site for photographers and other artists. Enjoy the view of the Bogey Hole from dawn till dusk every day.','Bogey Hole - Newcastle','','inherit','open','open','','221-revision-4','','','2012-10-12 13:21:16','2012-10-12 04:21:16','',22