 green parklands, restaurants, live entertainment and the activity of Australia’s oldest shipping port.\r\n\r\nThe seven precincts offer unique entertainment from each other. Enjoy the atmosphere at Carrington Precinct, have a picnic in the landscaped foreshore park, or take advantage of the walkway. Take in The Beacon public art in Linwood Precinct, go for casual café food at The Source Café, or take the path along Throsby Creek to neighbouring Tighes Hills. Go to Marina Precinct where the action is all happening and where the freshest of fresh seafood from the Fishermans Co-op can be found. Take in some of the history of Honeysuckle at Wickham Precinct with the Tree of Knowledge Park boasting one of the area’s oldest and most historic fig trees. You can enjoy the Cottage Creek Precinct, the commercial and residential hub of Honeysuckle where you can look at Nobbys headland in the distance or look out for international cruise ships and navy vessels. Go to Hunter Street Precinct for a colourful mix of commercial, retail and residential uses. Visit the Honeysuckle Precinct, the foremost social gathering place, with its collection of restaurants, cafes, public space, live entertainment and cultural activity making. You can find the Crowne Plaza Hotel, Habour Square, and The Boardwalk in the Honeysuckle Precinct.','Honeysuckle Harbour','','publish','open','closed','','honeysuckle-harbour','','','2012-10-12 16:14:02','2012-10-12 07:14:02','',311,'http://localhost/aus-newcastle/?page_id=326',0,'page','',0),(327,1,'2012-10-12 16:00:08','2012-10-12 07:00:08','The harbor is has seven precincts forming a 50 hectare site. It is an ongoing project of the residential and commercial urban renewal development of former industrial land along Newcastle Harbour, one of Australia’s largest urban renewal projects.\n\nEnjoy walks, ride or skate on the promenade stretches along the waterfront. Take in all the delights of the seven precincts of Honeysuckle which offers green parklands, r