popular swimming hole, <strong>Bogey Hole</strong>, a hand-hewn ocean rock pool carved out of a cliff face by convicts in the 19th century, in a spectacular scenic location When you’re done, enjoy a Newcastle’s ‘Live Sites\' event in Wheeler Place or Harbour Square.\r\n\r\nWalk along the <strong>Newcastle East Heritage Walk</strong> as you follow the steps of Newcastle\'s 205 year journey.\r\n\r\nFor reference on the preceding, <a href=\"http://www.visitnewcastle.com.au/pages/free-stuff/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>click here</strong></a>.\r\n\r\nRelax with the family picnic after you explore the wonders of nature in <a href=\"http://www.newcastle.nsw.gov.au/recreation/blackbutt_reserve\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Blackbutt Reserve</strong></a>, a great place to enjoy nature trails, wildlife exhibits, children’s playgrounds and recreational facilities. Just north of Newcastle nestled the K<strong>ooragang Nature Reserve, </strong>the largest single estuary wetlands reserve in NSW, a magnet for migratory shorebirds and there are good bird viewing areas near Stockton Bridge.\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.travelodge.com.au/travel-guides-free-things-to-do-in-newcastle\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>List of free things to do in Newcastle</strong></a>\r\n\r\nTake a self-guided tour around the barracks and above ground defense structures of the <a href=\"http://www.fortscratchley.com.au/tours/operating_hours\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Fort Scratchley</strong></a>. Admission Entry is free.\r\n\r\nListen to the live music at <strong>The Brewery</strong>, including DJ’s, every Wednesday, Friday, Saturday and Sunday. Or Visit the Pub Trivia at <strong>The Kent</strong>.','Free Things to do in the City of Newcastle','','publish','closed','closed','','free-things-to-do-in-the-city-of-newcastle','','','2012-10-14 01:25:13','2012-10-13 16:25:13','',435,'http://localhost/aus-newcastle/?page_id=464',0,'page','',0),(465,1,'2012-10-14 01:14:53','2012-10-13 16:14:53','','Free Things to do 